      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Standard Oil company is re-\nported to be concentrating deal\nfor the purchase of the immense coal\nfields owned by the Nicols Valley\nCoal and Iron company so miles north\nof the boundary line on the survey\nof the Nicola branch of\nthe Canadian Pacific and the Coast\nKootenai road of the Great Northern.\n\n\nThe property contains 1850 acres\nOF coal lands and the quality of the\ncoal mined Is said to be even better\nthan the famous Crows Net pass\nproduct. The consideration is said to\nbe S2.500,000 and the negotiations on\nthe part of the Standard Oil COM\npany are being conducted by NJ. X.\nRogers, the company's representative\nat Vancouver, b. c."
